workflow.name: Extract local business contacts with Google Sheets, SerpAPI, Apify & GPT-4o
workflow.description:
### Extract Local Business Contacts with Google Sheets, SerpAPI¬†&¬†GPT‚Äë4o

**Status:** Ready for Use‚ÄØ‚úÖ  
**Disclaimer:** This workflow relies on **community nodes** that are not part of n8n‚Äôs core package.  
Install the following from **n8n‚ÄØ‚Üí‚ÄØCommunity¬†Nodes** before running:

- **n8n-nodes-langchain**  
- **n8n-nodes-openai** (Structured¬†Output¬†Parser)  
- **n8n-nodes-apify**

---

### üìù¬†Description
This **n8n workflow** automates discovery of local‚Äëbusiness contact details by search term and location, then enriches the results with publicly listed email addresses using **GPT‚Äë4o¬†AI**.

---

### üîë¬†Key Features

#### üîó¬†Google¬†Sheets¬†Integration
- Reads search terms and locations from a Google Sheet.  
- Processes only rows that are **not** marked¬†`Complete`, preventing duplicates.

#### üó∫Ô∏è¬†Google¬†Maps Search via‚ÄØSerpAPI
- Queries Google¬†Maps through **SerpAPI** for every search‚Äëterm‚Äëand‚Äëlocation pair.  
- Retrieves the following fields: **business name, website, street address, and phone number**.

#### üß†¬†Website¬†Scraping¬†&¬†Email¬†Extraction
1. Scrapes the business homepage content with **Apify‚Äôs Fast Website Content Crawler**.  
2. Sends the scraped HTML to a **GPT‚Äë4o¬†AI¬†Agent**.  
3. Extracts any publicly listed **email address**.  
4. Returns a clean, structured JSON object for downstream use.

#### üíæ¬†Data¬†Storage¬†&¬†Tracking
- Writes every result to a **Results** tab in the same Google Sheet.  
- Marks the corresponding row in the **Searches** tab as `Complete` once finished.

#### üß±¬†Extensible¬†Design
The workflow uses modular sub‚Äëworkflows and AI agents.  
You can easily extend it to add:

- Phone‚Äënumber verification with Twilio  
- Social‚Äëmedia enrichment with Clearbit  
- Exports to **HubSpot**, **Salesforce**, **Airtable**, **PostgreSQL**, or CSV files

---

### üìÑ¬†Google¬†Sheet¬†Setup
Create a **Searches** tab with these exact columns (one header row):

Search | Area | Area Name | Complete

Create a results tab with these columns

title | website | address | phone | Search | Search Name | Area | email (Manual Entry)



---

### ‚öôÔ∏è¬†Prerequisites
1. **Google¬†Cloud¬†Project** with **Google Sheets API** and **Google Drive API** enabled  
2. **SerpAPI** account (free trial or paid) ‚Äì obtain an API key  
3. **Apify** account (free trial or paid) with the **Fast¬†Website¬†Content¬†Crawler** actor installed  
4. **OpenAI** account with an API key that can access GPT‚Äë4o models

---

### üöÄ¬†Setup¬†Instructions

1. **Copy the Google¬†Sheet**  
   - Make a personal copy of the template sheet.  
   - Ensure the tab names are **Searches** and **Results**.  
   - https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1QgcVMlXRlM_5ZFFUHr6bVK-93Tzia9XseTX03ZYnowI/edit?usp=sharing

2. **Configure Google¬†Sheets¬†nodes in n8n**  
   - Open the workflow.  
   - Update the nodes **Extract¬†Search¬†Terms** and **Save¬†Emails¬†to¬†Sheet** to point at your copied sheet.  
   - Authenticate using Google OAuth2 credentials that have access to the sheet.

3. **Add SerpAPI credentials**  
   - Sign in at <https://serpapi.com>.  
   - Copy your API key.  
   - In the **Search¬†Google¬†Maps** node, create a new credential and paste the key.

4. **Set up¬†Apify**  
   - Sign up at <https://apify.com>.  
   - Add the **Fast¬†Website¬†Content¬†Crawler** actor to your account.  
   - In the **Scrape¬†Web¬†Page** HTTP node, append `?token=YOUR_API_KEY` to the actor URL.

5. **Add your OpenAI¬†API key**  
   - Go to <https://platform.openai.com>.  
   - Generate an API key.  
   - Add it to the **AI¬†Agent** and **OpenAI¬†Chat¬†Model** node credentials.

---

### ‚úÖ¬†Running¬†the¬†Workflow
1. Click **Execute‚ÄØWorkflow** in n8n.  
2. For each unprocessed row in the **Searches** tab, the automation will:  
   1. Retrieve business information from Google¬†Maps via‚ÄØSerpAPI.  
   2. Scrape the business website using Apify.  
   3. Use GPT‚Äë4o to extract a public email address.  
   4. Write all collected data to the **Results** tab.  
   5. Mark the original row as `Complete`.

---

### üß©¬†Example¬†Use¬†Cases
- Build highly targeted lead lists for **sales** and **marketing** outreach.  
- Compile local business directories for regional websites or apps.  
- Automate contact‚Äëinformation collection for **lead‚Äëgeneration** campaigns and reduce manual data entry.

parameters.content:
## n8n Workflow: Local Business Contact Finder with Email Extraction

** Feel free to contact me if you need help implementing (rbreen@ynteractive.com) **

## How to Implement This n8n Workflow

Follow the steps below to get this business contact finder workflow up and running in your own environment:

1. Copy the Google Sheet
Make a copy of the search input/output sheet to your own Google Drive:

üëâ https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1QgcVMlXRlM_5ZFFUHr6bVK-93Tzia9XseTX03ZYnowI/edit?usp=sharing

2. Update the Google Sheets Nodes
Open the workflow in n8n.

Update both Google Sheets nodes ("Extract Search Terms" and "Save Emails to Sheet") to point to your copied sheet.

Make sure you select the correct sheet/tab names (Searches and Results).

Connect your Google account using the Google Sheets OAuth2 credentials.

3. Get a SerpAPI Key
Sign up for a free trial at üëâ https://serpapi.com/dashboard

Copy your API key.

In the ‚ÄúSearch Google Maps‚Äù node:

Click on credentials.

Add a new SerpAPI credential using your API key.

4. Set Up Apify Crawler
Sign up for an Apify account at üëâ https://apify.com

Go to the Actors section and add Fast Website Content Crawler to your account.

In the "Scrape Web Page" HTTP node:

Under credentials, enter your Apify API key as a query string parameter (token=YOUR_API_KEY).

5. Add Your OpenAI Key
Sign up at üëâ https://platform.openai.com/

Go to API keys and copy your secret key.

In the "AI Agent" (LangChain node) and "OpenAI Chat Model" nodes:

Add your OpenAI key under the OpenAI credentials section.

‚úÖ Once Complete:
Click "Execute Workflow" to run the automation. The script will:

Read a search + location from your Google Sheet.

Pull business info from Google Maps.

Visit each business‚Äôs website and scrape its content.

Use AI to extract an email address if available.

Save the full results into the "Results" tab and mark the search as complete.

data.details: The Execute Workflow node can be used when you want your workflow to treat another workflow as a step in your flow. It allows you to modularize your workflows and have a single source of truth for series of actions you perform often.
The Code node allows you to execute JavaScript in your workflow.

The Filter node can be used to filter items based on a condition. If the condition is met, the item will be passed on to the next node. If the condition is not met, the item will be omitted. Conditions can be combined together by AND(meet all conditions), or OR(meet at least one condition).
